== United States administrative law definitions ==
In [[United States administrative law]], the [[Code of Federal Regulations]]  (CFR)  '''Title 14, Aeronautics and Space''', also known as the '''[[Federal Aviation Regulations]]''', or FARs, are administered by the [[Federal Aviation Administration]].  Chapter II &ndash; Office of the Secretary, [[Department of Transportation]] (Aviation Proceedings)  Subchapter A &ndash; Economics regulations, Part 243 &ndash; Passenger manifest information, Section 243.3 ''Definitions'' (14 CFR 243.3) says: ''Air piracy'' means any seizure of or exercise of control over an aircraft, by force or violence or threat of force or violence, or by any other form of intimidation, and with wrongful intent. Subparagraph (3)  further defines an act of air piracy as an ''[[Air disaster]]''.<ref>{{cite web 
|url= http://www.law.cornell.edu/cfr/text/14/243.3
|title= 14 CFR 243.3 - Definitions 
