==Popular culture==

The Hollywood film [[Air Force One (film)]] starring [[Harrison Ford]] recounts the fictional story of the hijacking of the famous aircraft by six Kazakh ultra-nationalist terrorists.<ref>{{cite news| url=http://www.imdb.com/title/tt0118571/| title=Air Force One | author=IMDb| publisher=IMDb}}</ref>

The film [[Con Air]], starring [[Nicolas Cage]] and [[John Malkovich]], features scenes in which an aircraft is hijacked by the maximum-security prisoners on board.<ref>{{cite news| url=http://www.imdb.com/title/tt0118880/.   /| title=Con Air | author=IMDb| publisher=IMDb}}</ref>
[[The Taking of Flight 847: The Uli Derickson Story]] was a made-for-TV film based on the actual hijacking of TWA Flight 847, as seen through the eyes of the chief flight attendant [[Uli Derickson]].<ref>{{cite news| url=http://www.imdb.com/title/tt0096216/| title=The Taking of Flight 847: The Uli Derickson Story| author=IMDb| publisher=IMDb}}</ref>
[[Passenger 57]] is a film starring [[Wesley Snipes]] as an airline security expert trapped on a passenger jet when terrorists seize control.<ref>{{cite news| url=http://www.imdb.com/title/tt0105104/| title=Passenger 87| author=IMDb| publisher=IMDb}}</ref>

[[Skyjacked (film)]] is a 1972 film about a crazed Vietnam war veteran hijacking a Boeing 747 and demanding to be taken to Russia by the captain, [[Charlton Heston]] .<ref>{{cite news| url=http://www.imdb.com/title/tt0069278/| title=Skyjacked | author=IMDb| publisher=IMDb}}</ref>

The 1986 film [[The Delta Force]] starred [[Chuck Norris]] and [[Lee Marvin]] as leaders of an elite squad of special forces troops tasked with retaking a plane hijacked by Lebanese terrorists.
<ref>{{cite news| url=http://www.imdb.com/title/tt0090927/| title=The Delta Force | author=IMDb| publisher=IMDb}}</ref>

